###Block: Shugenja
# Ability Name			Unique Key							Category of Ability		Type									Description																																																				Auto Weapon Prof					Bonus DC							Source Page
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Shugenja ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Shugenja Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:Shugenjas are proficient with all simple weapons and with the short sword (wakizashi). They are not proficient with any armor nor with shields. Armor does not interfere with her spellcasting.																					AUTO:WEAPONPROF|Sword (Short)|TYPE=Simple									SOURCEPAGE:p.12
Element Focus (Air)		KEY:Shugenja ~ Element Focus (Air)			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Shugenja Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:Air spells are subtle, involving travel, intuition, influence, divination, and illusion. Earth is the prohibited element for air shugenjas.  The Order of the All-Seeing Eye and the Order of the Spring Zephyr specialize in air magic. They benefit from Spell Focus for the element air.												BONUS:DC|DESCRIPTOR.Air|1|TYPE=SpellFocus		SOURCEPAGE:p.13
Element Focus (Earth)		KEY:Shugenja ~ Element Focus (Earth)		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Shugenja Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:Earth spells are involve resilience and resolve, health and growth, and the strength of its body. Air is the prohibited element for earth shugenjas.  The Order of the Impenetrable Crucible and the Order of the Perfect Sculpture specialize in earth magic. They benefit from Spell Focus for the element earth.								BONUS:DC|DESCRIPTOR.Earth|1|TYPE=SpellFocus	SOURCEPAGE:p.13
Element Focus (Fire)		KEY:Shugenja ~ Element Focus (Fire)			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Shugenja Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:Fire spells are destructive and blatant, though they also deal with intelligence, inspiration and creativity. Water is the prohibited element for fire shugenjas.  The Order of the Consuming Flame specialize in fire magic. They benefit from Spell Focus for the element fire.														BONUS:DC|DESCRIPTOR.Fire|1|TYPE=SpellFocus	SOURCEPAGE:p.13
Element Focus (Water)		KEY:Shugenja ~ Element Focus (Water)		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Shugenja Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:Water spells involve transformation, cleansing, healing, and friendship. Fire is the prohibited element for water shugenjas.  The Order of the Forbidding Wasteland and the Order of the Gentle Rain specialize in water magic. They benefit from Spell Focus for the element water.														BONUS:DC|DESCRIPTOR.Water|1|TYPE=SpellFocus	SOURCEPAGE:p.13
Sense Elements			KEY:Shugenja ~ Sense Elements				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Shugenja Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	DESC:One of the first "spells" a shugenja learns-a magical effect so basic it becomes a spell-like ability-is to sense elements. As a full-round action, a shugenja can become aware of all sources of one chosen element (air, earth, fire, or water) within 10 feet of him. Spellcraft checks and time reveal more info.																SOURCEPAGE:p.13

###Block: Spirit Shaman
# Ability Name			Unique Key								Category of Ability		Type											Define				Innate Spells													Description																																																																									Template				Auto Armor Prof				Auto Shield Prof										Auto Weapon Prof																		Add 				Source Page
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:A spirit shaman is proficient with all the club, dagger, dart, handaxe, javelin, longspear, quarterstaff, shortspear, spear, sling, shortbow, throwing axe, and with light armor and shields. These are associated with tribal societies in which spirit shamans are found.																																		AUTO:ARMORPROF|ARMORTYPE=Light	AUTO:SHIELDPROF|SHIELDTYPE=Buckler|SHIELDTYPE=Heavy|SHIELDTYPE=Light	AUTO:WEAPONPROF|Club|Dagger|Dart|Handaxe|Javelin|Longspear|Quarterstaff|Shortspear|Spear|Sling|Shortbow|Axe (Throwing)					SOURCEPAGE:p.15
Spirit Guide			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Spirit Guide				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:All spirit shamans have a spirit guide, a personification of the spirit world. Unlike a familiar, a spirit guide is not a seperate entity from the shaman. She is the only one who can perceive it or interact with it. It exists only in her own mind and soul.																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.16	ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Alertness
Wild Empathy			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Wild Empathy				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																					DESC:Guided by her insight into animal spirits, a spirit shaman can use body language, vocalization, and demeanor to improve the attitude of an animal. This ability functions just like Diplomacy check made to improve a person's attitude. Use the d20+(CL+CHA) for the check. The range is 30 feet.																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.16
Chastise Spirits			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Chastise Spirits			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialAttack.Supernatural							SPELLS:Spirit Shaman Ability|TIMES=(3+CHA)|CASTERLEVEL=CL|Chastise Spirits,10+CL+CHA	DESC:Beginning at 2nd level, a spirit shaman can use divine energy granted by her patrons in the spirit world to damage hostile spirits. With a standard action, do (CL)d6 to all spirits within 30 ft. Affected creatures get a Will save (DC(10+CL+CHA)) for half damage. The ability can be used (3+CHA) times per day.																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Detect Spirits			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Detect Spirits				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike							SPELLS:Spirit Shaman Ability|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=CL|Detect Spirits				DESC:The spirit shaman's spirit guide perceives nearby spirits. At will, the spirit shaman can use detect spirits as a spell-like ability. It functions just like detect undead, except it detects creatures considered spirits.																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Blessing of the Spirits		KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Blessing of the Spirits		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike							SPELLS:Spirit Shaman Ability|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=CL|Blessing of the Spirits		DESC:Starting at 4th level, a spirit shaman can perform a special rite to gain a blessing. She meditates and travels in the spirit world. This takes 10 minutes. It wards her like protection from evil but against spirits and it lasts until it is dismissed or dispelled.																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Follow the Guide			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Follow the Guide			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																					DESC:At 5th level and higher, a spirit shaman's spirit guide helps her maintain control of her mind. If the shaman is affected by an enchantment spell or effect and fails her save, she can attempt it again 1 round later at the same DC. She only gets this one extra chance to succeed on her saving throw.																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Ghost Warrior			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Ghost Warrior				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																					DESC:Beginning at 6th level, a spirit shaman confers the ghost touch special ability to any weapon she holds as long as she holds it. She also becomes resistant to the touch attacks of incorporeal creatures, and may use her normal AC instead of her touch AC against their attacks.																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Warding of the Spirits		KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Warding of the Spirits		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike							SPELLS:Spirit Shaman Ability|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=CL|Warding of the Spirits			DESC:Starting at 7th level, a spirit shaman can perform a special rite once per day to ward herself and her companions against hostile spirits. Performing the rite takes 1 minute. The ward lasts for (CL*10) minutes and is otherwise like magic circle against evil, except protecting against spirits.																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Spirit Form				KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Spirit Form				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	DEFINE:SpiritFormsPerDay|0																DESC:At 9th level and higher, a spirit shaman learns how to temporarily transform herself into a spirit. Once per day, as a standard action, she can become incorporeal for up to 1 minute. She gains all benefits of the subtype for that minute. He AC while incorporeal is her CHA mod. At 15th level she can do this twice. At 20th, she can do this three times per day.																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.17	ASPECT:NAME|Spirit Form %1/day|SpiritFormsPerDay
Guide Magic				KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Guide Magic				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																					DESC:Starting at 10th level, as a free action, a spirit shaman can assign her spirit guide the task of concentrating to maintain a spell. The spirit makes concentration checks using the shaman's check. It can not be interrupted or interacted with, so it needs fewer checks.																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Recall Spirit			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Recall Spirit				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike																						DESC:At 11th level, a spirit shaman gains the ability to call back the spirit of a dead creature before it has completely left the body. Once per week, she can restore life  to a recently deceased creature. The ability must be used within 1 round of the victim's death. The ability works like raise dead, except causing no level loss, no Constitution loss, and no loss of spells. The creature is restored to -1 hit points (but is stabilized).																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Exorcism				KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Exorcism					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																					DESC:Starting at 13th level, as a full-round action, a spirit shaman can force a possessing creature or spirit out of the body it inhabits. To exorcise a possessing creature, she makes a class level check d20+(CL+CHA) vs a DC of 10 + HD + the creatures Charisma mod. If she wins, the exorcism worked. If it fails, it cannot be retried for the same victim for 24 hours.																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Weaken Spirits			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Weaken Spirits				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																					DESC:At 16th level and higher, a spirit shaman can strip spirits of their defenses by using a chastise spirits use. Weakened spirits loose their SR, DR, miss chance, and ability to move through objects. For each 3d6 damage not applied the spirits are weakened for 1 round. Spirits that make their Will save are unaffected by the weakening effect (but still take half the remaining damage).																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Spirit Journey			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Spirit Journey				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike							SPELLS:Spirit Shaman Ability|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=CL|Spirit Journey				DESC:A spirit shaman knows how to vanish bodily into the spirit world beginning at 17th level. This ability functions like the spell shadow walk, except that a shaman can only transport herself. She need not be in a shadowy area and travels through the Plane of Spirits, not the Plane of the Shadows. This is useable once per day.																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Favored of the Spirits		KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Favored of the Spirits		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike							SPELLS:Spirit Shaman Ability|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=CL|Favored of the Spirits			DESC:At 19th level, a spirit shaman learns how to perform a rite that guards her from death. The rite takes 8 hours and the shaman bargains away part of her life force, expending 1000 xp. The rite's effect lasts until it is dismissed or discharged. While under the protection of the rite, the shaman receives a heal spell equal to her caster level if she is reduced to 0 hp or lower. The protection is discharged once triggered.																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Spirit Who Walks			KEY:Spirit Shaman ~ Spirit Who Walks			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Spirit Shaman Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																					DESC:At 20th level, a spirit shaman becomes one with the spirit world. She is forevermore treated as a fey instead of a humanoid for purposes of spells and magical effects. Additionally, she gains damage reduction 5/cold iron.																																					TEMPLATE:Spirit Who Walks																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.18


